  "prompt": "What is a psychiatrist?",
  "response": "A psychiatrist is a medical doctor (M.D. or D.O.) who specializes in the diagnosis, treatment, and prevention of mental health disorders. Unlike psychologists, psychiatrists can prescribe medication and provide medical treatments. They are trained to:\n\n1. Assess mental health conditions\n2. Diagnose psychiatric disorders\n3. Prescribe and manage psychiatric medications\n4. Provide psychotherapy\n5. Offer treatments for conditions like depression, anxiety, bipolar disorder, schizophrenia, and other mental health issues\n6. Conduct medical examinations to understand the connection between mental and physical health\n\nPsychiatrists typically complete medical school, a psychiatric residency, and may pursue additional specialization in areas like child and adolescent psychiatry or geriatric psychiatry.",
